It's alleged that Julius Malema discharged the rifle during a rally in Mdantsane in 2018. JOHANNESBURG - Economic Freedom Fighters (EFF) leader Julius Malema is expected to appear in the East London Magistrates Court on Monday over the discharge of a firearm in a public space. It's alleged that Malema discharged the rifle during a rally in Mdantsane in 2018. He's facing five different charges, which include the unlawful possession of a firearm and reckless endangerment. The State is expected to handover video footage taken on the day to the defence team.